children.text: The balustrade wall in this area contains no lateral restraint or bracing to keep it securely into its vertical position and prevent it from movement.
The NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) states in section 3.9.2.3 Construction of barriers to prevent falls that ‘
A barrier must be designed to take loading forces in accordance with AS/NZS 1170.1’ .
Australian Standard AS 1170.1 in section 3.6 Barriers requires that all barriers be designed to sustain the imposed actions given in Table 3.3, below;
This must be properly rectified to ensure that it meets the minimum loading forces in accordance with the BCA and Australian standard AS 1170.
